g.text: Game Concept: Ramen Shop Simulator
An idle / shop management / tycoon responsive mobile web game built on Phaser.
The whole of the screen shows a ramen shop in isometric view, with the
entrance at the lower-right and a cut-off isometric view inside with a
ramen bar at the top left.
The topmost part of the screen shows a Popularity Bar.
The upper left of the screen shows how much cash the player has earned.
The upper-right of the screen shows the current day and time.
The bottom of the screen shows tabs:
Ingredients, Decorate, Stats, Settings
Selecting a tab will display a submenu allowing the player to do more operations.
Ingredients will show a list of ingredients, how much is currently in stock and a price,
pressing the ingredient will buy a new one.
Throughout the day, customers enter the shop and start heading towards the ramen bar.
Once they reach the ramen bar they request for a specific ramen dish that requires
a combination of specific ingredients.
If the player has the ingredients, the customer purchases the dish and the ingredients
are subtracted from the players' stock. The player earns cash and the popularity bar increases.
If the player doesn't have the ingredients, the customer is unable to buy and the
popularity bar decreases. The customer then starts leaving the shop and exiting towards
the lower left.
